FBIS3-56841 "drsov014_u_94005" FBIS-SOV-94-014 Document Type:Daily Report 21 Jan 1994 Latvia Talks Leader Criticizes Russia's `New Stance' LD1901195694 Riga Radio Riga Network in Latvian 1800 GMT 19 Jan 94 LD1901195694 Riga Radio Riga Network Language: Latvian Article Type:BFN [Text] The new stance of Russia, expressed by the Russian foreign minister on 18 January, will seriously hamper the Latvian-Russian talks on the withdrawal of troops from our country, according to Martins Virsis, parliamentary secretary at the Latvian Foreign Ministry and leader of the Latvian delegation in talks with Russia. He was speaking at a news conference today. According to information at the disposal of the Latvian Foreign Ministry, Kozyrev's statements have not yet been officially retracted.
